Data Overview 2

Data Source:
The data used for this analysis was sourced from data.gov. The power plant locations and characteristics are part of the California Energy Commission’s (CEC) California Energy Infrastructure geospatial data sets. The data is derived from the CEC’s QFER-1304 Power Plant Owner Reporting Database.

Key Metrics

System Architecture 
The project workflow involves analyzing California Power Plant data to identify trends and contributing factors, gathering relevant data from data.gov , cleansing and preprocessing the dataset, applying machine learning models to predict accident severity, performing in-depth analysis using DAX and Power BI, visualizing key insights through interactive dashboards, and providing data-driven recommendations to improve road safety and reduce accident severity.




Data Features
The dataset contains vital metrics like Plant Name, Location, Maintenance Status, Capacity, and Plant Age, each displayed with intuitive icons for easy interpretation. It also includes a 'Data Dictionary' that visually maps the relationships between attributes such as Primary Energy Source, Maintenance Needs, and Average Maintenance Probability. This highlights key factors such as Plant Age, Maintenance Probability, and Capacity, which are essential for understanding the operational health and longevity of power plants.
